Did you declare these variables? The assembler won't know what "addrLO" and "addrHI" mean unless you tell it. You can put in the beginning of your file something like this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">addrLO = $10<br />addrHI = $11</div><br />Make sure to not use addresses that are already in use by other variables.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Mon Mar 15, 2010 5:36 pm</p><hr />
